  "name": "Acts 7:54–60",
  "localizedName": "Acts 7:54–60",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Holy Spirit showed Stephen something in the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108529",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "heavenly world"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Stephen saw the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108557",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Son of Man"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " standing and ruling beside God. Jesus is the Son of Man."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Stephen told everyone what he saw. The Sanhedrin believed that Stephen was speaking against God. They were so angry that they killed him."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "As he died, Stephen followed Jesus’ example when he died on the cross. Jesus trusted his life to God (Luke 23:46). Stephen did the same. He trusted Jesus to care for his spirit when he died."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus asked God to forgive those who killed him (Luke 23:34). Stephen prayed that his attackers would be forgiven. In his life and in his death Stephen was completely faithful to his Lord."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
